flowRoot.flowPara: Difficult bug
Some bugs are notoriously hard to catch: race conditions, communication issues with 2+ servers, heisenbugs and more.
Unknown bug
Bugs that neither Python or you know about may stay in your code for longer.
Semantic error
There is no error message, but you see immediately that the outout is wrong.
Exception at runtime
Python attemts to execute the program but crashes with an error.
Syntax Error
Python is unable to read the code and refuses to do anything.
Debugger
Use pdb or ipdb to execute the program in slow motion, use breakpoints.
Minimize input
Create small and simple input data that you could compute manually.
Partition
Split the faulty code in half and find out which half contains the problem. Repeat.
Inspect internal state
print statements, a debugger or logging let you see what is happening.
Read error messages
Some error messages are helpful, some not. Read from the bottom.
Code review
Explain the problem to a colleague and ask them to take a look.
Take a break
Debugging does not work well at all
if you are tired or stressed.
